  "text": "Periodic twists were introduced in [CITATION_1] as a generalization of the spherical twists for projective modules over symmetric algebras described above. They were later used to study actions of longest elements in braid groups, using a lifting theorem, in [CITATION_2] . The construction given there is as follows. Suppose that A is a symmetric algebra and P is a projective A-module with endomorphism algebra E = End A (P)",
